"August 7, 2020, The Government of Lithuania announced that 5– 12 grade pupils will learn remotely (until 8 November) except for children educated in special institutions and special classes in general education schools. The necessary conditions for public health safety, hygiene, provision of persons with necessary personal protective equipment must be ensured: disinfection; 
hand hygiene (washing and/or disinfection); 
prohibition to work for employees with symptoms or if isolation is prescribed."

"August 7, 2020, The Lithuanian government announced that pre-school, pre-primary and primary education will continue the usual way. The necessary conditions for public health safety, hygiene, provision of persons with necessary personal protective equipment must be ensured: disinfection; 
hand hygiene (washing and/or disinfection); 
prohibition to work for employees with symptoms or if isolation is prescribed."

